  <reg:title>Regional District of <in:br/>Bulkley-Nechako Regulation</reg:title>
  <reg:amsincluded>[includes amendments up to B.C. Reg. 193/2001]</reg:amsincluded>
  <bcl:ccollect value="statreg_codes_solo"/>
  <reg:content>
    <bcl:section id="d2e42" toc="false">
      <bcl:marginalnote>Economic Development</bcl:marginalnote>
      <bcl:num>1</bcl:num>
      <bcl:text>The Regional District of Bulkley-Nechako is granted the additional power to provide Economic Development as an extended service.</bcl:text>
    </bcl:section>
    <bcl:section id="d2e54">
      <bcl:marginalnote>Para-Transit</bcl:marginalnote>
      <bcl:num>2</bcl:num>
      <bcl:text>The Regional District of Bulkley-Nechako is granted the additional power to provide Para-Transit as a local service.</bcl:text>
      <bcl:hnote>[en. B.C. Reg. 241/91.]</bcl:hnote>
    </bcl:section>
    <bcl:section id="d2e69">
      <bcl:marginalnote>Cemetery Grant-in-Aid</bcl:marginalnote>
      <bcl:num>3</bcl:num>
      <bcl:text>The Regional District of Bulkley-Nechako is granted the additional power to provide Cemetery Grant-in-Aid as a local service.</bcl:text>
      <bcl:hnote>[en. B.C. Reg. 169/92.]</bcl:hnote>
    </bcl:section>
    <bcl:section id="d2e84">
      <bcl:marginalnote>Electric Power Distribution</bcl:marginalnote>
      <bcl:num>4</bcl:num>
      <bcl:text>The Regional District of Bulkley-Nechako is granted the additional power to provide, as a local service, Electric Power Distribution to Birch Bay on Francois Lake.</bcl:text>
      <bcl:hnote>[en. B.C. Reg. 418/92.]</bcl:hnote>
    </bcl:section>
    <bcl:section id="d2e99">
      <bcl:marginalnote>Telephone Capital Financing</bcl:marginalnote>
      <bcl:num>5</bcl:num>
      <bcl:text>The Regional District of Bulkley-Nechako is granted the additional power to authorize the acquisition of Telephone Capital Financing as a local service.</bcl:text>
      <bcl:hnote>[en. B.C. Reg. 436/92.]</bcl:hnote>
    </bcl:section>
    <bcl:section id="d2e115">
      <bcl:marginalnote>Water diversion works and maintenance</bcl:marginalnote>
      <bcl:num>6</bcl:num>
      <bcl:text>The Regional District of Bulkley-Nechako is granted the additional power to establish a water diversion works and maintenance service specifically for the Glacier Gulch project, including the powers of a municipality under sections 551 and 552 of the <bcl:link resource="leg" xlink:href="/legislation/96323TC_01" xlink:type="locator"><in:doc>Municipal Act</in:doc></bcl:link><in:footnoteref>1</in:footnoteref>, as a local service.</bcl:text>
      <bcl:hnote>[en. B.C. Reg. 34/95.]</bcl:hnote>
    </bcl:section>
    <bcl:section id="d2e135">
      <bcl:marginalnote>
        <in:doc>Emergency Program Act</in:doc>
      </bcl:marginalnote>
      <bcl:num>7</bcl:num>
      <bcl:text>The Regional District of Bulkley-Nechako is granted the same power that a municipality has as a local authority under the <bcl:link resource="leg" xlink:href="/legislation/96111_01" xlink:type="locator"><in:doc>Emergency Program Act</in:doc></bcl:link>.</bcl:text>
      <bcl:hnote>[en. B.C. Reg. 193/2001.]</bcl:hnote>
    </bcl:section>
    <bcl:footnote>
      <bcl:num>1</bcl:num>
      <bcl:text>R.S.B.C 1996-323-551 and 552, repealed by 1999-37-121</bcl:text>
    </bcl:footnote>
    <reg:provisionsnote>[Provisions of the <in:doc>Local Government Act</in:doc>, R.S.B.C. 1996, c. 323, relevant to the enactment of this regulation: section 799]</reg:provisionsnote>
  </reg:content>
